\subsection{Step 5 --- Campaign C1: TX power sweep}
\begin{enumerate}[leftmargin=2em]
	\item Position Target~A 3~m from the Threat antenna. Target~B off, Threat button not held. C1 produces DATA-only rows from Beacon~ID \texttt{0x01}.
	\item TX power is controlled by \texttt{LORA\_TX\_PWR\_DBM} at the top of the \texttt{/* USER CODE BEGIN PD */} block in \texttt{Core/Src/main.c} of the \texttt{Nucleo\_RFM95\_TargetA} project. Change only this one define for each sweep step:

	\begin{center}
	\renewcommand{\arraystretch}{1.2}
	\begin{tabular}{cl}
		\toprule
		\textbf{Target TX power} & \textbf{Define to set} \\
		\midrule
		+2~dBm  & \texttt{\#define LORA\_TX\_PWR\_DBM  2} \\
		+8~dBm  & \texttt{\#define LORA\_TX\_PWR\_DBM  8} \\
		+14~dBm & \texttt{\#define LORA\_TX\_PWR\_DBM  14} \\
		+20~dBm & \texttt{\#define LORA\_TX\_PWR\_DBM  20} \\
		\bottomrule
	\end{tabular}
	\end{center}

	\item For each power level:
	\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=1.2em]
		\item Update \texttt{LORA\_TX\_PWR\_DBM} in \texttt{main.c}, press \textbf{F7} to build, then \textbf{F5} to flash and run.
		\item Confirm on the USART2 debug terminal that the board prints \texttt{lora\_init done: SF=7 TxPwr=\textit{N} dBm} with the expected power level before collecting.
		\item Run \texttt{python collect.py}, select the matching C1 entry from the menu (e.g.\ \emph{C1 TX Power Sweep --- +2 dBm}), enter the COM port for Board~1, and accept or type the output filename. Collect 200 packets.
		\item Wait for the script to report ``Done.'' Do not interrupt mid-run.
	\end{itemize}
	\item The four runs produce four separate CSV files. Name them \texttt{c1\_pwr02.csv}, \texttt{c1\_pwr08.csv}, \texttt{c1\_pwr14.csv}, \texttt{c1\_pwr20.csv} (override the default filename at the output prompt if desired).
\end{enumerate}

